olive oil
1 carrot
½ tin sweetcorn
1 packet beef strips
1 packet couscous
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
¾ cup boiling water
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet Smokey Aioli
1 sachet Chimichurri Seasoning

• Boil the kettle. Slice carrot into thin half-moons. Drain sweetcorn
(see ingredients).
• In a medium bowl, combine chimichurri seasoning, a drizzle of olive oil
and a pinch of salt. Add beef strips and toss to coat. Set aside.
• In a medium heatproof bowl, add couscous, chicken-style stock powder
and a drizzle of olive oil. Add the boiling water (3/4 cup for 2 people / 1 1/2
cups for 4 people) and stir to combine. Immediately cover with a plate and
leave for 5 minutes. Fluff up with a fork.
• When couscous is done, add baby spinach leaves. Toss to combine and
season to taste.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat.
• Cook carrot and sweetcorn, tossing, until tender and browned,
4-5 minutes. Transfer to a large bowl.

• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. When oil
is hot, cook beef strips in batches, until browned and cooked through,
1-2 minutes.
• Transfer to bowl with veggies. Toss to combine. Season with salt
and pepper.

TIP: Cooking the meat in batches over high heat helps it stay tender.

• Divide spinach couscous between bowls.
• Top with chimichurri beef and veggies.
• Serve with smokey aioli. Enjoy!